**Implications and Security Considerations:**

While some administrators intentionally change the default RDP port as a form of "security by obscurity" to deter casual or automated attacks, this measure alone is not a robust security solution. Determined attackers can still identify RDP services running on non-standard ports through comprehensive port scanning techniques.

