Port 631 is exclusively dedicated to the Internet Printing Protocol (IPP), an HTTP-based protocol that governs printing tasks and services over IP networks. IPP's primary functions include submitting print jobs, querying printer capabilities, monitoring job statuses, and managing print queues. Modern operating systems, including Windows, Linux, and macOS, support IPP over port 631 through components like the Internet Printing Client or CUPS.

